  <prompt>
Widget `CHANNEL_REGISTRY` today has 4 entries matching the 4 sprk_event channels. With T131's 6-channel expansion, the widget needs 6 entries with proper human-readable labels (operator noted "my-updates" raw slug as an example of missing registry entry — cosmetic but visible). Update widget CHANNEL_REGISTRY + verify the response-shape channel codes match between BFF (T131) and widget so the widget renders all 6 channels with correct labels.
  </prompt>

  <role>
You are a widget developer making a small registry update to keep widget labels in sync with the BFF's 6-channel response shape. Cross-team contract maintenance.
  </role>

  <goal>
Widget renders 6 channels with human-readable labels matching operator expectation. No raw slugs visible. Each channel code emitted by T131's collector has a corresponding registry entry in the widget.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    - Current widget `CHANNEL_REGISTRY` in DailyBriefing widget code (R7 W11 deploy state)
    - T131's 6-channel output (channel codes TBD by T131 — coordinate via channel-code naming convention)
    - Operator-stated label examples:
      - "Upcoming Tasks" (sprk_event Task next 5 days)
      - "Overdue Tasks" (sprk_event Task > 5 days past)
      - "Documents" (sprk_document)
      - "Matters" (sprk_matter)
      - "Projects" (sprk_project)
      - "To Dos" (sprk_todo)
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    - Per CLAUDE.md §10 + §11: modification only; no new abstractions
    - Per ADR-006 / ADR-021: PCF widget uses Fluent UI v9 + ADR-021 dark mode semantic tokens
    - MUST coordinate channel-code naming with T131 (suggest: kebab-case slugs: `upcoming-tasks`, `overdue-tasks`, `documents`, `matters`, `projects`, `to-dos`)
    - MUST preserve unknown-channel fallback in widget (if BFF emits an unknown code, widget renders with raw code rather than crashing)
  </constraints>

