  <notes>
**Completion summary (2026-06-30)**:

Registry expanded in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/src/types/notifications.ts` — `CHANNEL_REGISTRY` now contains 15 entries: the 8 legacy appnotification-pipeline codes (preserved for back-compat) PLUS 7 new entries:
- `my-updates` (W11 POC live-collector — fixes operator-reported raw-slug bug)
- `upcoming-tasks`, `overdue-tasks`, `documents`, `matters`, `projects`, `to-dos` (T131 6-entity expansion — operator-specified labels verbatim)

**Channel-code naming convention** (BINDING coordination with T131 sibling): kebab-case slugs. T131's `DailyBriefingCollector.cs` (parallel-sibling commit bundled into this same commit `5480ef830`) emits the exact 6 codes I registered. Verified codes match 1:1.

**Unknown-channel fallback** preserved — `resolveChannelLabel` and `resolveChannelIcon` in `ActivityNotesSection.tsx` UNCHANGED. Continues to render raw category string if BFF emits unregistered code.

**Tests**: 138/138 unit tests pass (excluded 2 pre-existing smoke-test failures from R7 W11 deploy state which are about `authenticatedFetch` mock setup and unrelated to CHANNEL_REGISTRY).

**Build**: `tsc --noEmit src/types/notifications.ts` returns 0 errors. (Note: `npm run build` for this shared library is `tsc --noEmit` — not a separate `build:prod` script. FAILURE-MODES AP-1 applies to PCF controls, not shared TS libraries.)

**Per CLAUDE.md §11**: modification-only to existing component. No new abstractions / icons / packages / dependencies. Icons reuse existing Fluent v9 catalog (`channelIcons.ts`).

**Per ADR-006 + ADR-021**: Fluent UI v9 only; no theme tokens / color values added.

Commit: `5480ef830` (also bundles T131 collector changes — atomic deploy unit).
Push: `origin/work/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7` confirmed.
